	18.2 Common mistakes
From wiki: http://dom3.servegame.com/wiki/Common_mistakes

Ideas
Not contacting other players/nations but staying silent in MP games, diplomacy is key

Pre-game
Not working out a long term strategy before the game begins
Not taking an awake combat pretender when playing a nation with weak national troops.
Not taking the time to work out a pretender design with a long term strategy in mind.
Not raising Dominion to "safe levels", but only picking strong magics (newbie mistake)

Early game
Not expanding fast enough
Recruiting low quality indep troops to spend extra gold
Attacking strong independents without a good plan

Movement
When attacking a province, sneaking into a province with some of your commanders by mistake (can be avoided by ctrl+clicking to move)
Not accounting for water-based movement onto land
Not taking into account an enemy's ability to sail or fly or cloud trapeze or teleport
Not knowing all the neighbor connections from a province

Provincial Defense
If you do not buy any PD, it's easy for an opponent to take a whole bunch of provinces from you just using scouts. Buy at least 1PD everywhere
If you spend too much on PD you'll waste gold that could be better put to use expanding

Combat
Failure to decoy archers (use of a few troops in front and to the of others to draw fire)
Forgetting to separate troops with harmful auras (heat, poison, chill) from their vulnerable allies
Getting your super combatant commanders killed by forgetting to script them properly
Not providing an avenue of retreat for your army

